"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424503","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-02","<p>The Government is planning to encourage long-term share ownership in Lloyds shares, offering the incentive of bonus shares for longer-term investors.</p><br /><p>Lloyds Banking Group (LBG) remains a commercial company in which the Government is currently a shareholder. The Government’s shareholding is managed at arm’s length from HM Treasury by UK Financial Investments (UKFI). The Government does not involve itself in the commercial decisions of LBG. Whether or not to pay dividends to its shareholders is a commercial decision to be made by the bank’s independent management team.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-11-02T16:09:12.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424503/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424503/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424503/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-28","Lloyds Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will hold discussions with Lloyds Bank on that company prioritising the payment of dividends to encourage small shareholders to retain shares for the long term, in advance of further sales of the Government's stake in that company.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","13762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424504","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-05","<p>The Government will put in place transitional protection to ensure that individuals with savings over the proposed lifetime allowance limit are not subject to retrospective taxation. Further detail on these protections is provided at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pension-schemes-newsletter-73-october-2015/pension-schemes-newsletter-73-october-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pension-schemes-newsletter-73-october-2015/pension-schemes-newsletter-73-october-2015</a></p><p><br></p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-11-05T15:42:11.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424504/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424504/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424504/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-28","Personal Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, following his decision to reduce the lifetime allowance for those saving with personal pensions, what assistance the Government plans to offer to people whose additional pension provision is likely to breach the reduced lifetime allowance for personal pensions but would not have breached the previous limit.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","13757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424505","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-03","<p>None. This is a matter for the partnerships concerned.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-11-03T16:54:15.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424505/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424505/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424505/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-28","Roads: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the level of democratic oversight of road safety partnerships; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","13832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424506","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-02","<p>This is not a matter for the Department for Communities and Local Government.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-11-02T16:57:03.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424506/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424506/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424506/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Take-away Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether he plans to change how take-away food delivery drivers are regulated.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","13753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424507","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-05","<p>The Government is committed to building 200,000 starter homes over the course of this Parliament to provide affordable homes for purchase with 20% discount are available to first time buyers under 40.</p><p>The Government remains committed to delivering 275,000 new affordable homes between 2015 and 2020. This means we will build more new affordable homes than during any equivalent period in the last twenty years.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-11-05T16:38:08.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424507/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424507/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424507/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many (a) starter and (b) affordable homes the Government plans to build over the next five years.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","13738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424508","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-04","<p>I have been asked to reply on behalf of the Home Office.</p><p>Fire and rescue services in England reported almost 24,300 visits which they defined as “fire setter and anti-social behaviour schemes and other youth diversion visits” in 2013/14, although not all services were able to provide figures. They also reported almost 24,000 visits defined as “other youth fire safety programmes”.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-02-04T14:09:41.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424508/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424508/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424508/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Young People: Crime Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many Youth Diversion events were undertaken by English fire and rescue services in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","13914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424509","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-04","<p>I have been asked to reply on behalf of the Home Office.</p><p>Fire and rescue services carried out almost 67,300 Fire Safety Audits / Inspections in 2013/14.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-02-04T14:08:52.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424509/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424509/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424509/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many statutory Fire Safety Inspections were carried out by English fire and rescue services in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","13915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424510","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-04","<p>Statistics on additional housing for affordable rent provided in each local authority area in England are published in the Department’s live table 1006a which is available at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-affordable-housing-supply</p><p>These figures include both newly built housing and acquisitions.</p><p>Figures are not collected on the basis of Parliamentary constituencies.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","13873","2015-11-04T14:31:14.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424510/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424510/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424510/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Affordable Housing: Bristol South","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many new homes for affordable rent were completed in Bristol South constituency in each year from 2010 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","13872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424511","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-04","<p>Statistics on additional housing for affordable rent provided in each local authority area in England are published in the Department’s live table 1006a which is available at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-affordable-housing-supply</p><p>These figures include both newly built housing and acquisitions.</p><p>Figures are not collected on the basis of Parliamentary constituencies.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","13872","2015-11-04T14:31:14.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424511/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424511/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424511/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Social Rented Housing: Bristol South","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many new homes for social rent were completed in Bristol South constituency in each year from 2010 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","13873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424512","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-05","<p>The Government has committed, through the Productivity Plan, to introduce a dispute resolution mechanism to speed up section 106 negotiations to enable housing and other development to be built more quickly. We intend to do this through the Housing and Planning Bill.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-11-05T16:37:09.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424512/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424512/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424512/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Affordable Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will change planning procedures for local authorities to speed up the construction of new affordable homes to buy.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","13874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424513","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-04","<p>We will consider the case carefully for exceptions from the policy and will set out the detail in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-11-04T14:29:01.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424513/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424513/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424513/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will provide exemptions from the pay to stay scheme for tenants in affordable rent-to-buy properties.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","13875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424514","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-02","<p>Statistics on house building starts and completions are not available by parliamentary constituency.</p><p>These statistics for England and for each local authority district, including Bristol, are published in the Department's live tables 253 (annual) and 253a (quarterly), which are available at the following link:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-house-building" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-house-building<br></a></p><p>The house building statistics exclude other sources of housing supply such as conversions.</p><br />","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-11-02T16:57:47.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424514/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424514/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424514/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Housing: Bristol South","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many homes were completed in Bristol South constituency in each year from 2010 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","13941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424515","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-06","<p>Information on the number of full time equivalent firefighter posts for each fire and rescue service and for each year, together with greater detail, is available in the Department’s Fire and Rescue Operational Statistics publication (Table 2 for full time equivalent posts) at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fire-and-rescue-authorities-operational-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fire-and-rescue-authorities-operational-statistics</a></p><br />","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","13946 ; 13948","2015-11-06T13:37:06.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424515/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424515/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424515/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Devon and Somerset Fire and Rescue Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what change there has been in the number of firefighter posts was in Devon and Somerset Fire and Rescue Service in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","13938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424516","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-05","<p>Trade union membership levels are a matter for the trade unions.</p><p>The Cabinet Office publishes data relating to Civil Service facility time on a quarterly basis. The latest data is Quarter 4, 2014 at and is available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time</a></p><p>In the Department for Communities and Local Government, during 2014/2015 total spend on facility time was £73,667 and 2,571 hours of facility time was claimed by trade union representatives.</p><p>Facility time spend during 2015/16 (April to September) currently stands at £46,851 and 1,581 hours of facility time was claimed by trade union representatives.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-11-05T16:36:33.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424516/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424516/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424516/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Department for Communities and Local Government: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many civil servants in his Department are members of trades unions; how much working hours facility time is claimed by each such civil servant; and what the cost of that facility time is to his Department.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","13896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424517","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-11","<p>In 2013/14 fire and rescue services in England attended over 28,100 road traffic collisions. They also attended over 1,200 other transport incidents.</p><p>This information for all fire and rescue services, together with greater detail and more up-to-date data (for 2014/15), is available in the Department’s Fire Statistics Monitor publication (Table 7):</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fire-statistics-monitor-april-2014-to-march-2015</p><p /> <br />","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2015-12-11T12:51:49.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424517/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424517/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424517/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Fire Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many road traffic collisions English fire and rescue service attended in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","13947"
