"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424519","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-06","<p>Information on the number of full time equivalent firefighter posts for each fire and rescue service and for each year, together with greater detail, is available in the Department’s Fire and Rescue Operational Statistics publication (Table 2 for full time equivalent posts) at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fire-and-rescue-authorities-operational-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/fire-and-rescue-authorities-operational-statistics</a></p><br />","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","13938 ; 13946","2015-11-06T13:37:05.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424519/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424519/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424519/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Avon Fire and Rescue Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the change in the number of firefighter posts was in Avon Fire and Rescue Service in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","13948"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424520","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-03","<p>The licence obligation on Telefonica to provide indoor 4G coverage to 98% of the UK population by 2017 does not include coverage in tunnels.The Government recognises that dropped calls and intermittent access to the internet are frustrations felt by many rail passengers. The Government is working with the rail and telecommunications industries to reach a collective understanding of the technical and commercial challenges and the potential solution to this problem.</p><br />","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-03T12:11:34.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424520/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424520/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424520/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-28","Telefonica: Underground Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 27 October 2015 to Question 12790, whether the licence obligation on Telefonica to provide indoor 4G coverage to 98 per cent of UK premises by 2017 includes coverage in tunnels.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","13926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424521","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-09","<p>The Department does not actively collect information around trade union memberships.</p><br /><p>The Cabinet Office publishes data relating to Civil Service facility time on a quarterly basis. The latest data is Quarter 4, 2014 at and is available at<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time</a>.&quot;</p><br />","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-09T15:25:38.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424521/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424521/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424521/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-28","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many civil servants in his Department are members of trades unions; how much working hours facility time is claimed by each such civil servant; and what the cost of that facility time is to his Department.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","13897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424522","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-03","<p>The Government has provided £780 million to support the roll-out of superfast broadband to 95 per cent of homes and businesses in the UK. In addition we are supporting seven pilot projects to explore ways to extend superfast broadband beyond 95 per cent of UK home and businesses.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-03T12:10:05.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424522/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424522/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424522/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-28","Broadband: Small Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to ensure that small businesses are able to access high speed broadband.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","13876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424524","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-12","<p>The Government remains committed to delivering a reformed Electronic Communications Code that is clear, fit for purpose, and supports a UK network that provides consumers with a choice of high quality telecommunications services.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-12T16:37:45.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424524/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424524/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424524/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-28","Telecommunications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans his Department has to reform the Electronic Communications Code following the closure of the consultation on 30 April 2015.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","13839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424525","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-02","<p>My Department has no plans to commemorate the 350th anniversary of the passage into law of the Nonconformists Act 1665.</p><p>The Nonconformist Act was rightly repealed in 1689.</p><p>Freedom of speech, freedom of worship, democracy, the rule of law, and equal rights define us as a society. The Government is determined to promote these values actively, working in partnership and alongside all communities.</p><br />","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-11-02T16:59:08.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424525/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424525/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424525/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-28","Five Mile Act 1665","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will take steps to commemorate the 350th anniversary of the passage into law of the Five Mile Act 1665.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","13859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424527","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-02","<p>I am in regular contact with The Football Association on a number of issues, including good governance and reform of FIFA. The Football Association are in regular contact with their Home Nation counterparts.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-11-02T18:24:24.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424527/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424527/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-28","FIFA: Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will discuss with the four home nations football associations allegations of corruption within FIFA and steps to rebuild public confidence in the administration of international football.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","13760"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424528","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-09","<p>The Government's superfast broadband programme is aimed at achieving availability of superfast broadband to 95% of UK premises by December 2017. The funding allocations to the English local authorities and the devolved administrations have been made on the basis of maximising overall UK coverage,and the Phase 2 allocations that were made in February 2014 also had a minimum allocation for each devolved administration based on the Barnett formula.</p><br />","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-09T15:59:25.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424528/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424528/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424528/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-28","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will hold discussions with each of the devolved administrations on ensuring that the roll-out of superfast broadband benefits people across the UK uniformly.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","13756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424529","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-10","<p>Access to broadband is of vital importance to small businesses, which is why the Government-funded Broadband Connection Voucher Scheme has provided over 50,000 small and medium sized enterprises with access to high speed broadband.83 per cent of homes and businesses already have access to superfast broadband services, and thanks to the Government's investment in the superfast broadband rollout. This is set to rise to 95 per cent by the end of 2017.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-10T16:29:29.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424529/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424529/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-28","Broadband: Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will estimate the cost to businesses of inconsistent broadband coverage in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","13814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424530","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-12","<p>This Government is ensuring that all children have the opportunity to experience a broad selection of art and cultural activities regardless of where they live or go to school. Since 2012, the Government has invested over £460 million in music and cultural education programmes. In addition, publicly funded arts organisations across the country run excellent education programmes to help children experience the arts, including the Arts Council's Cultural Education Challenge, which encourages the local cultural education partnerships. The Department for Culture, Media and Sport also funds the Heritage Schools Programme to help schools across the country make use of their local historic environment.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-12T16:44:05.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424530/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424530/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424530/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-28","Cultural Heritage: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans his Department has to improve access for children in rural areas to high-quality cultural and historical exhibits.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","13812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424531","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-02","<p>This information is not held.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-02T16:50:03.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424531/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424531/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424531/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-28","Ministry of Defence: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of senior civil servants in his Department are from a lower socio-economic background.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424532","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-02","<br /><p>I and my Ministerial colleagues expect to continue to have periodic discussions with the Canadian Defence Minister, once appointed, and relevant colleagues and officials on a range of issues including future Royal Canadian Air Force procurement policy.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-02T16:45:02.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424532/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424532/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424532/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-28","Air Force: Canada","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to hold discussions with the Canadian government on future Royal Canadian Air Force procurement policy.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","13819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424533","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-05","<p>Members of the MOD Saudi Armed Forces Projects (MODSAP) and Saudi Arabian National Guard Communications (SANGCOM) Project attend a mandatory bribery and fraud awareness workshop which explains current legislation in this area, assists members to understand their responsibilities under the provisions of the legislation and identifies areas of risk of bribery and fraud within the workplace. This training highlights the statutory protection against dismissal and victimisation provided to whistleblowers under the provisions of the Public Disclosure Act 1998 and provides advice on reporting suspicious activity.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-05T15:29:43.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424533/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424533/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424533/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-28","Ministry of Defence: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what training is provided to officials of his Department working on the Ministry of Defence Saudi Armed Forces Programme and the Saudi Arabia National Guard Communications Project on responding to whistleblowers from the private sector.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","13794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424534","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-04","<p>Babcock is a key supplier to the Ministry of Defenceand the company's relationship with the Department is managed at a strategic level through a key supplier representative. This role is currently undertaken by the Chief of Materiel (Fleet) within Defence Equipment and Support, who engages with Babcock on a regular basis. Project and safety performance reviews form a significant element of these discussions.</p><p>With regards to safety, appropriate measures are in place to reduce risk and these are rigorously monitored to ensure that any emerging issues are identified and addressed.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-04T15:28:02.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424534/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424534/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-28","Babcock International","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what arrangements are in place to monitor Babcock's performance and safety record.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","13845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424535","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-04","<br /><br /><p>All radioactive waste arising from the decommissioning of nuclear-powered submarines at Rosyth will be transported off-site either for recycling, direct disposal, or storage in an interim storage facility as part of the Submarine Dismantling Project.</p><p>For certain components, a temporary holding facility may be required on site; this short-term holding and all other activities will be fully regulated by nuclear safety and environmental regulators.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-11-04T15:29:08.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424535/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424535/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424535/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-28","Rosyth Dockyard: Radioactive Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to safely store or treat nuclear contaminated material arising from the decommissioning of nuclear-powered submarines at Rosyth by Babcock.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","13846"
