"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424693","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-11-03T13:30:16.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424693/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424693/answer","PQ13816.pdf","PQ13816.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Resident in Bristol","UKSA Letter to Member - Resident in Bristol","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424693/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-28","Termination of Employment: Bristol South","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of people resident in Bristol South constituency whose employment was terminated through ill health in each year from 2005 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","13816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424694","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-02","<p>The budget allocated for Flexible Support Fund in 14/15 was £136m [excluding the support contract which was a further £20m]. Spend was £72m, leaving an underspend of £64m</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-02T13:20:04.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424694/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424694/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424694/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-28","Flexible Support Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what budget was allocated to the Flexible Support Fund in the most recent financial year for which data is available; and how much of that budget remained unspent.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","13804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424695","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-02","<p>Official statistics record starts to sector-based work academy pre-employment training only. The Department does not collate information on outcomes, nor the number of benefit claimants finding work through a sector-based work academy placement. There are no current plans to do so.</p><br /><p>Official statistics are available on GOV.UK at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/youth-contract-april-2012-to-may-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/youth-contract-april-2012-to-may-2015</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","13765","2015-11-02T11:21:50.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424695/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424695/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424695/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-28","Employment Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of people who started employment through the Work Based Sector Academy scheme were still in employment with the same organisation after 13 weeks since that scheme began.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","13764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424696","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-02","<p>Official statistics record starts to sector-based work academy pre-employment training only. The Department does not collate information on outcomes, nor the number of benefit claimants finding work through a sector-based work academy placement. There are no current plans to do so.</p><br /><p>Official statistics are available on GOV.UK at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/youth-contract-april-2012-to-may-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/youth-contract-april-2012-to-may-2015</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","13764","2015-11-02T11:21:50.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424696/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424696/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424696/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-28","Employment Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has to monitor sustained employment through the Work Based Sector Employment scheme beyond 13 week follow-up enquiries to employers.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","13765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424697","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-06","<p>Work is the best route out of poverty, which is why this government is focused on getting people into employment.</p><p>With over 2 million more people in work since 2010, and the highest employment rate on record, significant progress has been made.</p><p>The latest figures show that there are 200,000 fewer people in working families that are in relative low income, than at its peak in 2008/09.</p><p>The latest figures also show that there are half-a-million more people living in working families and not in relative low income than in the previous year.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-11-06T14:36:31.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424697/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424697/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424697/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-10-28","Employment: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment his Department has made of trends in in-work poverty.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","13813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424698","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-10","<p>Highways England report that the incident occurred around 2:15 am, with the carriageway fully reopened by 9:25 pm. Diversions were initially put in place from junction 25 of the M1, with traffic diverted onto the A52 westbound, the A5111 southbound, the A6 southbound and the A50 eastbound, to re-join the M1 at junction 24. Unfortunately, there was a second incident on the slip road of the M1 at junction 25, resulting in a lane being closed. This meant the M1 closure was extended further north to junction 26 until this incident was cleared.</p><br /><p>Variable Message Signs were set prior to junction 38, in order to encourage drivers to divert via the A38. In addition, messages were displayed on the M62, A1(M), M18, A46, A52 and A38.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-11-10T12:20:50.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424698/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424698/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424698/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-28","M1: Accidents","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, following the accident on the M1 on 12 October, how long it took the Highways Agency to reopen junction 25 on the southbound carriageways, and how far north diversions were put in place.","false","Biography information for Lord Blunkett",,"Lord Blunkett","HL3068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424699","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-10","<p>Highways England reports that Junction 15 to 16: traffic management was lifted in September 2015 and Junction 16 to 19: traffic management will be lifted in stages. It will be completely removed by the end of November 2015.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-11-10T12:21:20.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424699/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424699/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424699/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-28","M1: Speed Limits","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when the 50 mile per hour limit on the M1 between junctions 19 and 15 will be lifted, in the light of the fact that work there has been suspended.","false","Biography information for Lord Blunkett",,"Lord Blunkett","HL3069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424700","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-05","<p>The UK remains committed to a sustainable political settlement that leads to a political transition in Syria, away from Assad, to a government in Damascus which better meets the needs of the Syrian people and with which we can work to defeat extremism. The Geneva Communiqué, which has been agreed by key international parties, remains a key building block of our efforts on this. On 30 October the UK, US, Russia, key Middle East states and European partners met in Vienna to take forward discussions on this. The Vienna Communiqué sets out areas of agreement and may provide the basis for a new process. The parties have agreed to reconvene within the next two weeks.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-11-05T16:07:53.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424700/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424700/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424700/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-10-28","Syria: Peace Negotiations","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether there are any new initiatives planned to revive or replace the so-called Geneva Two process on Syria.","false","Biography information for Baroness Helic",,"Baroness Helic","HL3070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424701","Department of Health","false","2015-11-06","<p>The World Health Organization published its conclusions on the carcinogenicity of eating red and processed meat on 26 October. The detailed evaluations will be published in the future; until these are available, we cannot assess them in detail.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2015-11-06T09:01:04.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424701/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424701/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424701/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-28","Cancer: Meat Products","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the World Health Organization research showing that eating processed meat increases the risk of cancer.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Whitchurch",,"Baroness Jones of Whitchurch","HL3071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424702","Department of Health","false","2015-11-06","<p>Public Health England’s advice is that, on average, people should be eating no more than 70 grammes of red and processed meat a day. People who eat a lot of these meats are at higher risk of bowel cancer than those who eat small amounts. Therefore, people who eat more than 90 grammes of red or processed meat a day are advised to cut down.</p><p><strong></strong></p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2015-11-06T09:01:29.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424702/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424702/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424702/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-28","Health Hazards: Meat Products","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what advice they are giving to consumers about the health risks of eating processed meat.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Whitchurch",,"Baroness Jones of Whitchurch","HL3072"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424703","Department of Health","false","2015-11-06","<p>The evidence base relating to dietary sodium intake was extensively reviewed in the Scientific Advisory Committee on Nutrition’s (SACN) report ‘Salt and Health’, published in 2003. In reviewing the evidence, SACN noted that the greatest benefits were likely to be achieved by taking a population approach to reducing salt intakes rather than through individual targeted advice.</p><br /><p>The SACN continues to monitor average salt intakes through a programme of dietary survey work.</p><br /><p>New voluntary salt reduction targets have been developed for 76 specific food groups that contribute most to people’s salt intakes and major retailers, manufacturers and caterers are working to meet these targets by December 2017.</p><br /><p>The SACN has also reviewed the evidence around the impact of low sodium intakes. It found no basis for changing the existing recommendation for a target reduction in average salt intake to 6 grammes per day for the adult population, equivalent to 2.4 grammes per day of sodium.</p><br /><p>The SACN ‘Salt and Health’ report is attached and can be found at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sacn-salt-and-health-report" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/sacn-salt-and-health-report</a></p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL3074 ; HL3075","2015-11-06T09:00:36.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424703/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424703/answer","SACN Salt and Health report 2003.pdf","SACN Salt and Health report 2003.pdf","Salt and Health","Salt and Health","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424703/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-28","Salt","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they last reviewed the evidence base relating to dietary sodium intake as part of a balanced diet.","false","Biography information for Baroness Masham of Ilton",,"Baroness Masham of Ilton","HL3073"
