"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424706","Home Office","false","2015-11-11","<p>The numbers of new cases received by the independent Investigatory Powers Tribunal each year are published on the Tribunal’s website at: http://www.ipt-uk.com/section.aspx?pageid=5 .</p><p>The numbers of complaints and claims for the years 2010 to 2014 are as follows.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Human Rights Claims</p></td><td><p>Complaints</p></td><td><p>Both</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>49</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>75</p></td><td><p>164</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>46</p></td><td><p>46</p></td><td><p>88</p></td><td><p>180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>37</p></td><td><p>52</p></td><td><p>79</p></td><td><p>168</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>58</p></td><td><p>67</p></td><td><p>80</p></td><td><p>205</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>58</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>97</p></td><td><p>215</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The Investigatory Powers Tribunal does not collate the information about the average length of time from a complaint or claim being submitted to the announcement of a ruling. The cases received by the Investigatory Powers Tribunal vary in scope and complexity. Each case is considered on its own merits and receives appropriate legal scrutiny.</p>",,"Lord Bates","HL3077","2015-11-11T17:27:09.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424706/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424706/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424706/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-28","Surveillance: Complaints","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many (1) complaints, and (2) claims, were submitted to the Investigatory Powers Tribunal in each year from 2010 to 2014 inclusive.","false","Biography information for Lord Marks of Henley-on-Thames",,"Lord Marks of Henley-on-Thames","HL3