"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424206","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-05","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Written Ministerial Statements of the 17 July [HLWS134] and 17 September [HCWS209]. As set out in the Ministerial Code, the Prime Minister is responsible for the overall organisation of the executive.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-05T09:28:18.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424206/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424206/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-27","Ministry of Justice: Departmental Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, for what reasons the Ministry of Justice no longer has responsibility for Government policy on freedom of information and data protection.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","13702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424207","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-10-30","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not collect data on all discussions between public organisations and Saudi Arabia. More broadly however, the British Government cooperates with Saudi Arabia in a large number of areas such as education, energy, security, defence, trade, culture and the challenges facing the Middle East.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-10-30T16:45:17.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424207/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424207/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-10-27","Saudi Arabia: Public Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, which public organisations are currently holding discussions with Saudi Arabia on carrying out work for that government.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","13619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424208","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-02","<p>There is an ongoing review into the most effective and appropriate definition for social mobility which we will align with in future years. This work is being led by The Bridge Group, a charitable policy association promoting social mobility, as part of research they are undertaking on social mobility in the Fast Stream.This research is the largest quantitative analysis of its kind and will help to inform how we define and measure social mobility across all Civil Service talent schemes, including the Future Leaders Scheme and Senior Leaders Scheme. The research will also help us to determine what information we collate and publish on these schemes in a meaningful and accessible way.</p><p>We are also working towards a position where we collate and publish diversity data in a single format on the <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">gov.uk</a>website to improve transparency and accountability on overall progress towards diversity and inclusion in the Civil Service.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-02T14:10:04.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424208/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424208/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424208/answer/previousversion/26904","Biography information for Matt Hancock","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-27","Civil Servants: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 26 October 2015 to Question 12401, if he will publish the socio-economic data collected for the 2015 intake of the Future Leaders Scheme and Senior Leaders Scheme.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424209","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-02","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-11-02T14:08:37.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424209/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424209/answer","CO-DC00-PRN01_Emman Chowdhury_4150_001.pdf ; PQ 13714.pdf","CO-DC00-PRN01_Emman Chowdhury_4150_001.pdf ; PQ 13714.pdf","Referrel Answer for Member - Mortality Rate ; UKSA Letter to Member - Mortality Rate","Referrel Answer for Member - Mortality Rate ; UKSA Letter to Member - Mortality Rate","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424209/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-27","Mental Illness: Mortality Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which psychiatric disorder had the highest mortality rate in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","13714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424210","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-02","<p>The arrangements for the determination of special advisers’ pay are set out in the Model Contract for Special Advisers.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-02T14:10:24.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424210/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424210/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424210/answer/previousversion/26902","Biography information for Matt Hancock","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-27","Special Advisers Remuneration Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 27 October 2015 to Question 13086, whether the Special Advisers Remuneration Committee still exists.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424211","Cabinet Office","false","2015-10-30","<p>Details of discussions with foreign governments are not usually disclosed.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-10-30T12:34:56.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424211/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424211/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424211/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-27","Foreign Relations: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, on how many occasions in each of the last five years officials of his Department have contacted representatives of a foreign government to ask for an account of private meetings or discussions held between representatives of that government and Scottish Government ministers.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","13634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424212","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-04","<p>The number of civil servants who are trade union members is a matter for individual trade unions.</p><p>The Cabinet Office publishes data relating to Civil Service facility time on a quarterly basis. The latest published data is for Quarters 1-4, 2014 and is available at:<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time</a></p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-04T10:04:39.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424212/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424212/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-27","Cabinet Office: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many civil servants in his Department are members of trades unions; how many working hours of facility time are taken by such civil servants; and what estimate he has made of the cost of that facility time to his Department.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","13734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424213","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-04","<p>Information relating to the number of HM Treasury staff who are members of Trade Unions is a matter for the relevant trade unions.</p><br /><p>The Cabinet Office publishes data relating to Civil Service facility time on a quarterly basis. The latest data is Quarter 4, 2014 at and is available at https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-union-facility-time.</p><br />","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-11-04T12:54:58.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424213/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424213/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424213/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-27","Treasury: Trade Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many civil servants of his Department are members of trades unions; how many working hours of facility time are taken by such civil servants; and what estimate he has made of the cost of that facility time to his Department.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","13733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424214","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-03","<p>The Government has committed to invest £100bn in infrastructure over the course of this Parliament. There are 31 projects and programmes in the East of England in the National Infrastructure Pipeline, which include the energy, transport and waste sectors. The Pipeline is a strategic overview of the level of public and private infrastructure investment planned over the rest of this decade and beyond. These projects and programmes have a total capital value of more than £6 billion, of which more than £2.5 billion is public spending.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-11-03T12:33:39.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424214/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424214/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424214/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-27","Infrastructure: Suffolk","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what fiscal support his Department is giving to infrastructure initiatives in East Suffolk.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr   Poulter","13662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424215","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-04","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) undertakes a wide range of work to protect customers from websites which attempt to unlawfully obtain information. This includes:</p><br /><ul><li>maintaining a portfolio of domains which could be used to confuse customers</li><li>proactively monitoring the internet daily to identify sites which infringe on the brand, and taking appropriate legal action against them</li><li>providing a mailbox service for the reporting of suspected phishing emails and websites. <br> <p>HMRC's pages on GOV.UK make clear that Concentrix works on behalf of HMRC, and that some tax credits customers will receive a letter showing both logos. Neither HMRC, nor agencies working for HMRC, will ever ask for online banking or other information via email or over the phone that would enable an unauthorised person to access bank accounts or otherwise commit fraud.</li></ul>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-04T17:35:10.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424215/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424215/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-27","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the quality of the information available for HM Revenue and Customs claimants to distinguish between genuine communications from Concentrix and phishing scams.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart McDonald","13712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424217","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-04","<p>In September 2014 The Government published data on the socio-economic status of recent entrants to the SCS</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/359079/socialmobility_revised.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/359079/socialmobility_revised.pdf</a></p><p>There is an ongoing review into the most effective and appropriate definition for social mobility which we will align with in future years. This work is being led by The Bridge Group, a charitable policy association promoting social mobility, as part of research they are undertaking on social mobility in the Fast Stream. The Outcome of this review will also inform future datacollection on socio-economic status more widely and assist us in our further efforts to increase representation of people from less well-off backgrounds at all levels within the civil service.</p><br />","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-11-04T17:32:59.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424217/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424217/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-27","Treasury: Senior Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of senior civil servants from his Department are from a lower socio-economic background.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424218","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-04","<p>Nationality is not a condition of entitlement to tax credits. The information requested is, therefore, not available.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-11-04T12:52:48.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424218/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424218/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-27","Working Tax Credit: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 26 October 2015 to Question 12792, for what reason the nationality of EU citizens in receipt of working tax credits is not recorded; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Stewart Jackson","Peterborough","Mr Stewart Jackson","13721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424219","HM Treasury","false","2015-10-30","<p>This Government is committed to moving from a high welfare, high tax, low wage economy to a lower welfare, lower tax, higher wage society. As the Chancellor made clear on [Monday / 26 October], the Government will set out at Autumn Statement how we plan to achieve the same goal of reforming tax credits, saving the money we need to save to secure our economy, while at the same time helping in the transition.</p><br /><p>The Summer Budget offered a new deal for working people. A new National Living Wage for workers aged 25 and above, initially set at £7.20 per hour from April 2016, will directly benefit 2.7 million low wage workers, and up to 6 million could see a pay rise as a result of a ripple effect up the earnings distribution. The new National Living Wage will boost pay for those currently earning the National Minimum Wage by £4,800 a year by 2020 when the National Living Wage is expected to rise to over £9 per hour.</p><br /><p>To help working families keep more of what they earn, the personal allowance will increase to £11,000 in 2016-17 and £11,200 in 2017-18. The government has committed to increase the personal allowance to £12,500 by 2020 which will mean that a typical basic rate taxpayer will see their income tax cut by £1,205 a year compared to 2010.</p><br /><p>The government set out its assessment of the impacts of the Summer Budget policies in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill on 20th July 2015.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","13527 ; 13610","2015-10-30T14:20:11.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424219/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/424219/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-27","Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to lines 41 and 42 of Table 2.1 of the Summer Budget 2015 Red Book (HC 264), page 73, what the savings to the public purse would be if those measures were to be applied only to households that are not currently in receipt of tax credits or universal credit.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","13719"
